'''Shannon Lynn McRandle''' (born as Shannon Lynn Jones in Killeen, Texas, US) is a professional model, picked by [[Lucasfilm]] to represent [[Mara Jade Skywalker|Mara Jade]] in the photos taken for the ''[[Star Wars]]'' card games.

==Biography==
{{Quote|She is a big, bold character. Strong, self efficient, beautiful, smart. Who wouldn't like her. I loved reading about her and was very happy being asked to portray her. She really set the goal for the female characters in the SW Universe! I liked her best when she was Darkside, least when she was getting married&hellip; I thought the fussing over the wedding dress in the comic was a little unlike her. She was most fun when she was trying to kick Luke's butt!|Shannon McRandle about Mara Jade|<ref name="Interview">{{WebCite|url=http://yildizsavaslari.com/inceleme/shannonmcrandle/index_english.html|text=Shannon McRandle Interview|nolive=1|archivedate=20131126102153}}</ref>}}
Before [[1998]], [[Mara Jade Skywalker|Mara Jade]] appeared only as an illustration, but after that, illustrations attempted to simulate McRandle's look. According to the short story ''[[Sleight of Hand: The Tale of Mara Jade]]'', Mara Jade was present in [[Jabba's Palace/Legends|Jabba's Palace]] in the guise of Arica while [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]] was held captive. Before the release of the ''Star Wars'' DVDs, there was a rumor that Shannon was to appear in the Special Edition version of [[Star Wars: Episode VI Return of the Jedi|''Return of the Jedi'']] as a cameo. However, this did not occur.<ref>{{InsiderCite|66|Ask Lobot}}</ref>

Shannon has said that a small part in the movies for fun for the fans sounds great. She has stated her displeasure with ''[[Legacy of the Force: Sacrifice]]'', where Mara dies. She has stated that her given displeasure to ''Sacrifice'' is that if a person was able to kill off Mara Jade, that should have been Timothy Zahn, Mara Jade's creator.<ref>{{WebCite|url=https://www.starwarsnewsnet.com/2015/11/interview-with-the-real-mara-jade-shannon-mcrandle.html|text=INTERVIEW WITH THE REAL MARA JADE, SHANNON MCRANDLE.|author=Mill, Trevor|date=2015-11-22|work=Star Wars News Net|quote=No, I don't want them to mess with her anymore. [[Timothy Zahn|Tim (Zahn)]] wrote the most amazing character. She was BADASS! Very cool! Very smart! Yey! Then somewhere down the road, someone killed her after torturing her with unbelievable plot lines for a while and gave her the dumbest, most random [[death]], not befitting the character she was or had grown to be. I have always said if she HAD to die, Tim should have been the one to kill her. Let it lie. Please, just let it be! I trust [[The Walt Disney Company|Disney's]] judgment for now!|archivedate=20191108033111}}</ref>

